AddressInfo.AccessComments: Go to 17th floor, office just outside elevator TWO times: Just after parking and say you parked an electric car (present the ticket you got from the machine at entry). They will write EV on your ticket (in Chinese). Go there the SECOND time, when you want to leave again, then you have 15 minutes to exit. HINT: Have one person exit the car after you get the ticket, AND have passed the gate. That person brings ticket to 17/F (quite close to entry gate), while the driver goes to level 11 (for Tesla Superchargers) or level 11/12 for other chargers. It might have a read light on the street saying "Parking Full" despite empty spots inside (especially for charging)

GeneralComments: 32A single phase charging, 3.5 times faster than the usual 13A BS1363. Requires EV-link chip to activate. You need your own Type-2 cable (the thick blue cable that comes with Tesla Model S), and it will lock in the charging station as well - requires the EV-link to unlock the cable again (or using the E-charge app from HK EVpower. Parking is 16HKD/hr on weekdays, 13HKD/h on weekends and public holidays. With 32A charging, it's worth it, take a walk to the Lai Chi Kok MTR near by and leave the car charging while doing your business, charging at around 32 km/h (Tesla Model S). Staff seem very focused on the chargers not being blocked by ICE cars, not even by an EV NOT charging. I wasn't even done parking when a staff member came to ask 1) are you parking and 2) will you be charging.

GeneralComments: Enter parking BEFORE 11pm, after that you can leave any time. These Tesla supercharger bays are NOT currently reserved for Tesla cars (according to management, October 1st, 2014), and are NOT marked in any way to prevent any car to park there. Hopefully this will change any time soon. Spot 2B seems to be the fastest one at the moment, some have clocked over 600 km/hr initial charging (100+ kW).

AddressInfo.Title: Kai Tak Cruise Terminal
AddressInfo.Country.Title: Hong Kong
AddressInfo.AccessComments: Arrive before 11pm! After 11pm, no access, but one can leave any time. From the roundabout, drive to the end of the terminal (ground level), then at the 180 degree turn at the end, go up the ramp, keep to the right side (past the bus area) until there is a parking lot entry on the left side. After the gate (use Octopus or Visa only), go to the end for 13A chargers, continue clockwise around to find 4 Supercharger stalls (Tesla Motors)

GeneralComments:
Contributors Note: 
VERY complicated procedure, charging didn't work (25 Sep 2014) ,difficult walking access between parking-shroff-mall, very narrow inside, both turns and spots (apart from charging spots, plenty room there). With no power, went back up to entrance (very long walk), they gave me a key, with which I could open the installation box. A timer was inside, it was set to on. I tried both boxes, neither gave any power. It seems like it was turned off remotely, maybe at the fuse panel somewhere. After 15 minutes I gave up, to got to Phase 1 (much better, and very close by). They still charged me 12 HKD, despite I told them the charger didn't work, and I had to leave again. AVOID AT ALL COST until this is fixed (report back here please)

GeneralComments: Go to 17th floor, office just outside elevator TWO times: Just after parking and say you parked an electric car (present the ticket you got from the machine at entry). They will write EV on your ticket (in Chinese). Go there the SECOND time, when you want to leave again, then you have 15 minutes to exit. HINT: Have one person exit the car after you get the ticket, AND have passed the gate. That person brings ticket to 17/F (quite close to entry gate), while the driver goes to level 11 (for Tesla Superchargers) or level 11/12 for other chargers. It might have a read light on the street saying "Parking Full" despite empty spots inside (especially for charging)

AddressInfo.AccessComments: 24 hours. From the road entry, pass the main entrance (note the office for ticket payments just after main doors on your left, you will need it later). Just before exit back to road, turn right and DOWN into the entry for the car park. You start on 17th floor, keep going DOWN until 11th floor. Note a lot of traps of going "wrong way", keep turning (right), don't go straight (into "wrong way"), all the way down to 11/F

GeneralComments: This is a combined CCS/ChaDeMo/AC charging spot, up to 50 kW charging. Both the parking and use is free (November 2015). Tried it with a BMW i3, using CCS, and I got around 34 kW (probably limited by the car). I didn't try the AC or ChaDeMo. AC says 43 kW, not sure which connector it actually is. For access: Drive up to the gate, and wait for security to see you. They will open the gate and help you into the spot (you have to park right up against the wall). They are very helpful, and it's totally free.
